    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102640</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>Tyler mixes 5 teaspoons of sugar with 2 teaspoons of cinnamon to make 1 batch of cookie topping.</p>

<ol>
	<li>Draw a diagram showing the ratio of sugar to cinnamon.</li>
	<li>How much sugar and cinnamon would Tyler need for 2, 3, and 4 batches of cookie topping?</li>
</ol>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><ol>
	<li>Answers vary. Sample response:
	<p><img class="h-max-height--5-lines" src="/image_files/30671.png" /></p>
	</li>
	<li>The amounts of sugar and cinnamon needed would be 10 and 4 teaspoons, 15 and 6 teaspoons, 20 and 8 teaspoons, respectively.</li>
</ol>
</div>
